title: New Certificate and Masters Degree in Machine Learning and Artificial Intelligence for Engineering!!
description:
https://www.engr.washington.edu/admission/professional-masters-certificates/artificial-intelligence-and-machine-learning-certificate

The Graduate Certificate in Artificial Intelligence (AI) and Machine Learning (ML) for Engineering equips engineers to use modern data-driven AI and ML methods. This certificate can be completed independently or combined with other eligible data-intensive certificates in the College of Engineering to create a stacked Master of Science in Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning for Engineering.

This certificate is designed for engineers who want to apply modern AI and ML methods to their field, particularly for applications with physical constraints, such as manufacturing, chemical processes, or robotics. Students will advance their careers by building on their traditional engineering expertise and learn how to apply data-driven techniques to engineering use cases.

title: What happens if AI just keeps getting smarter?
description:
Join the movement to protect humanityâ€™s future: https://controlai.com/take-action

In this video, we extrapolate the future of AI (Artificial Intelligence) progress, following a timeline that starts from todayâ€™s chatbots to future AI thatâ€™s vastly smarter than all of humanity combinedâ€“with God-like capabilities. In particular, we show how, based on current trends, AI will likely become AGI (Artificial General Intelligence), which in turn will be able to aid with AI progress and self-improve, leading to ASI (Artificial Superintelligence) and ultimately to "God-like" AI. Such AI will pose a significant existential risk to humanity.

This video was made in partnership with ControlAI, a nonprofit that cares deeply about humanity surviving the coming intelligence explosion. They are mobilizing experts, politicians, and concerned citizens like you to keep humanity in control. We need you: every voice matters, every action counts, and weâ€™re running out of time.

title: IA MEMBUAT RUMAH PERI DIDEPAN RUMAHNYAâ—#videoviral #kreatif #keren
description:
Suatu hari saat gadis ini bangun dan melihat dari jendela, para pekerja sedang membongkar trotoar lama dan mulai memasang yang baru. Saat trotoar digali, akar sebuah pohon besar terpotong. Wanita itu melihatnya dan menemukan sepasang kaki kecil mendekati area tersebut. Setelah itu dia memutuskan untuk membangun sebuah rumah peri di sana. Tanpa menunggu lama, ia langsung mulai bekerja. Ia merancang sebuah pintu kecil yang indah dan mendesain ruangan mungil di antara akar pohon. Tak lupa, ia menambahkan sebuah lampu kecil di depannya. Tapi ini belum selesai. Keesokan paginya ia melihat jejak kaki mungil di sekitar rumah itu tampaknya seseorang sudah menemukannya. Ia pun bergegas menyelesaikan karyanya. Ia menambahkan rambu pengaman kecil berupa kerucut. Mulai menata landskap dan muncullah ide kreatif lainnya. Ia menggunakan balok beton kecil berisi baja sebagai batu pavingnya. Lalu menaburkan rumput di sekitarnya untuk menambah nuansa alami. Kini gambarannya sudah lengkap. Sebuah rumah peri mungil, cantik, dan penuh imajinasi. Keesokan harinya, anak-anak mulai memperhatikan rumah itu. Beberapa diantara mereka bahkan membawa barang-barang kecil untuk menambah isi rumah peri tersebut. Mereka berharap akan ada peri sungguhan yang datang kerumah itu.

title: Wie KÃ¼nstliche Intelligenz die Bildung verÃ¤ndert | Markus Lanz vom 18. Juni 2024
description:
Suchmaschinen wie Google waren gestern, heute krempeln KI-Anwendungen wie ChatGPT das deutsche Bildungswesen krÃ¤ftig um. Mit dem Chatbot kann man quasi eine normale Unterhaltung fÃ¼hren, in Sekundenschnelle spuckt er Antworten auf gestellte Fragen aus - und das auch in Echtzeit und heimlich im Klassenzimmer. 

"Die entscheidende Frage ist nicht mehr: 'Wird KI in die Schule kommen?' Das ist lÃ¤ngst entschieden", sagt Florian Fabricius. Der ehemalige GeneralsekretÃ¤r der BundesschÃ¼lerkonferenz erlebt im Klassenzimmer lÃ¤ngst zwei Welten: Auf der einen Seite, die SchÃ¼lerinnen und SchÃ¼ler die KI-Anwendungen wie ChatGPT wie selbstverstÃ¤ndlich benutzen â€“ auf der anderen Seite: LehrkrÃ¤fte, die glauben, dass "KI in 50 Jahren die Gesellschaft verÃ¤ndern wird".  Eine fatale Situation, so der 18-JÃ¤hrige Abiturient aus Hessen. Denn in Zeiten, in denen viele mehr Medienbildung einforderten, frage er sich, wer den SchÃ¼lern diese beibringen soll. "Wir haben gerade die Situation, dass die LehrkrÃ¤fte viel weniger wissen als wir und wir mÃ¼ssten eigentlich den LehrkrÃ¤ften beibringen, wie es geht?"

Eine Sorge, die Bestseller-Autorin Silke MÃ¼ller teilt. Die erste Digitalbotschafterin des Landes Niedersachsen warnt davor, dass im Schulwesen "ein GefÃ¼hl vorhanden" ist, dass man abgehÃ¤ngt werde. Sie erlebe im Unterricht sowohl experimentierfreudige Lehrer - als auch welche, die KI in der Schule ganz verbieten wollen. MÃ¼ller spricht sich fÃ¼r einen Systemwechsel aus: "Wir haben eine charmante Ruinenverwaltung, die 200 Jahre alt ist. Das Schulsystem von jetzt erfÃ¼llt die AnsprÃ¼che von heute und von morgen." KI biete die Chance, mehr Zeit fÃ¼r SchÃ¼ler zu haben. 
Auch der Digitalexperte Sascha Lobo sagt: "Im Kern folgt die Didaktik von heute noch im Buchwesen." Er plÃ¤diert dafÃ¼r, mit KI Ã¼ber dialogische Formen der Bildung nachzudenken.

Den gesamten Talk findet ihr hier: https://kurz.zdf.de/JS9k/

_____
Hier auf ZDFheute Nachrichten erfahrt ihr, was auf der Welt passiert und was uns alle etwas angeht: Wir sorgen fÃ¼r Durchblick in der Nachrichtenwelt, erklÃ¤ren die HintergrÃ¼nde und gehen auf gesellschaftliche Debatten ein. Diskutiert in Livestreams mit uns und bildet euch eure eigene Meinung mit den Fakten, die wir euch prÃ¤sentieren.
Abonniert unseren Kanal, um nichts mehr zu verpassen.

Immer auf dem aktuellen Stand seid ihr auf http://www.ZDFheute.de/.

title: This is The Hottest Job in Tech No One Told You About
description:
Artificial Intelligence is changing everythingâ€”including who builds it. In this interview, I sit down with Mehrnoosh Sameki, a principal AI PM at Microsoft, to break down one of the fastest-rising roles in tech: the AI Product Manager.
We talk about what AI PMs actually do, why they matter more than ever, and how YOU can break into this fieldâ€”even without a technical background. 
From responsible AI to the future of work, this conversation is packed with real-world insights and advice.
MAIDAP (Microsoft AI Development Acceleration Program) https://www.microsoftnewengland.com/maidap/
Metaâ€™s RPM (Rotational Product Manager) program
https://www.metacareers.com/careerprograms/pathways/rpm
Grace Hopper https://ghc.anitab.org/

â­ï¸About Mehrnoosh
========================
Mehrnoosh Sameki (https://www.linkedin.com/in/mehrnoosh-sameki) is a Principal AI PM at Microsoft, where she leads the Generative AI evaluation team focused on building and implementing Responsible AI tools within Azure AI Studio. She is a co-founder of several open-source AI ethics tools, including Fairlearn, Error Analysis, and the Responsible AI Toolbox. Beyond her work at Microsoft, Mehrnoosh serves as a curriculum developer and lecturer with Break Through Tech, helping underrepresented women pursue careers in data science. 

â­ï¸About Jean
========================
Iâ€™m Jeanâ€”founder of Exaltitude with over 20 years in tech. I was the 19th software engineer at WhatsApp before its $19B acquisition by Meta and later led engineering teams at Meta, witnessing firsthand how technology evolves and shapes the world. 
Now, Iâ€™m on a mission to break down how AI is transforming careers, industries, and the future of work. With AI revolutionizing how we work, learn, and live, I simplify these concepts to make them accessible to everyoneâ€”whether you're starting in tech, pivoting careers, or curious about AIâ€™s impact. 
No hype. No jargon. Just real-world insights for navigating AI and whatâ€™s next.

description:

100% free ai tools  ğŸ‘‰ https://youtu.be/0kKdcLTq-qg Give a touch to your video using PopPop AI's free text to speech https://cutt.ly/3rpEnu7e and free sound effect generator https://cutt.ly/RrpEnHBc

Create Stunning 3D Animation Videos Using Free AI â€“ Step-by-Step Tutorial
https://youtu.be/Dgkmds_tvmI

Ready to create stunning 3D animation story videos using free AI tools? ğŸš€ In this video, Iâ€™ll guide you step-by-step through the entire processâ€”from crafting your story to publishing a professional animation. Whether you're a beginner or an experienced creator, this tutorial has everything you need to bring your ideas to life! ğŸŒŸ

ğŸ“‹ Step-by-Step Process
1ï¸âƒ£ Crafting the Story:

Start with a rough outline of your story.
Use ChatGPT to polish and enhance your script.
Divide the story into 24 scenes (or as many as you like).
2ï¸âƒ£ Generating Image Prompts:

Use ChatGPT to create detailed image prompts for each scene.
Save the character appearance prompts for consistency.
3ï¸âƒ£ Creating Images:

Open Leonardo AI and use the Phoenix 0.9 model.
Copy and paste the prompts into Leonardo AI and generate high-quality images for each scene.
4ï¸âƒ£ Converting Images to Videos:

Use Kling AI to convert images into video scenes quickly.
Generate smooth and visually appealing transitions.
5ï¸âƒ£ Editing with CapCut:

Import all video clips into CapCut.
Add transitions, sound effects, background music, and text to refine your animation.
6ï¸âƒ£ Adding Voiceovers with Eleven Labs:

Write a script and generate professional voiceovers using Eleven Labs.
Sync the voiceover with your video in CapCut for a polished final product.

write a short story of max finds a small dragon egg in the forest and take it at home the a small baby dragon is ached from the egg max name the dragon leo and then leo grows into big dragon and they playing in village one day some loe is out in the forest and some hunters starts pursuit and traps leo they catch leo it huge cage max searching for leo and finds him caged he at night unlock the cage   and the  hunter finds out about max free leo . both and leo and max fight hunters and defeats them comes home back

now convert the story into 24 scenes 
 
3rd  prompt 

Write detailed image prompts for each scene of story, describing the visuals in a way that fits an animated video. Ensure the main character's appearance remains consistent throughout the story. For instance, if the main character is a tiger, describe it consistently as "a brave orange tiger with black stripes and a kind smile" in every scene to maintain visual continuity. title: We Saved 100 Children's Hearts in Africa
description:
Light AI [http://light.ai/] is on a mission to deliver relevant solutions for the global healthcare community by leveraging assistive artificial intelligence.  Check out their incredible initiative at light.ai to learn more about their efforts. Light AI is a public company that currently trades on the Canadian CBOE/NEO exchange under $ALGO.NE and trades in the US under $OHCFF.  Together we are taking a step toward reducing the impact of heart disease!   

With your support, we will partner with Light AI to provide healthcare professionals in underserved areas with the tools they need to quickly diagnose Strep A and combat heart disease.  Please visit https://www.beastphilanthropy.org/campaign/we-saved-100-childrens-lives-in-africa to learn more.  

This incredible program is possible thanks to so many incredible partners.  As weâ€™ve said before, Beast Philanthropy is ALL OF US.  

Thanks to the following amazing people:

Thank you to the team at Hospitals for Humanity, especially Dr. Segun, and all of the families who so bravely allow us to tell their story.  Your courage and your bravery are praiseworthy!  To learn more about Hospitals for Humanity and donate directly to support their work, please visit: https://hospitalsforhumanity.org/donate/

We also want to thank Outside The Box Capital for facilitating this partnership between us and Light AI. To learn more go to [http://outsidethebox.capital]  

And thanks to you, our viewers.  None of this is possible without you!

Filmed and Edited by: Dan Mace  (https://www.youtube.com/@DanMace)

Microsoft Copilot Tutorial
description:
In this step-by-step tutorial, learn how to use Microsoft Copilot. We'll explore how to use Copilot in Windows, in Microsoft 365 apps like Word, PowerPoint, Outlook, and Excel, and on the web. By the end of this training, you'll know exactly what Copilot is and how to use it.

You might have noticed a new icon appearing just about everywhereâ€”on the taskbar in Windows, in apps like Word, PowerPoint, Teams, in your Edge browser, and even on your keyboard. But what exactly is it, and should you start incorporating it into your daily workflows? In this video, we're going to explore how Microsoft Copilot can transform your day-to-day tasks so you can work both smarter and faster. Whether you're drafting emails, crafting documents, or managing data, Copilot is here to assist you. Your workflows are about to get significantly better.

You'll Learn:
âœ… What is Microsoft Copilot?
Discover how to access and interact with Copilot through various methods such as the taskbar, keyboard shortcuts, and dedicated keys. Learn how Copilot functions as your everyday AI companion, remembering the context of your conversations to provide seamless assistance.

âœ… Using Copilot for Text and Image Generation:
See how Copilot can help you generate text-based responses and even create images based on your prompts. Explore the use of plugins to extend Copilot's capabilities for tasks like finding recipes, booking flights, and creating songs.

âœ… Copilot in Microsoft 365 Apps:
Understand how Copilot integrates with Microsoft Outlook to help you manage your inbox, summarize emails, and draft replies. Watch how Copilot assists in PowerPoint by creating presentations and refining slide designs. Learn how Copilot can rewrite text in Microsoft Word, making it more professional and concise. See how Copilot helps analyze data in Microsoft Excel, from applying conditional formatting to generating charts.

title: Machine learning to develop ROMs for the Navierâ€“Stokes equations
description:
In this video, we explore how machine learning techniques can be used to develop reduced-order models (ROMs) for the Navierâ€“Stokes equations, the cornerstone of fluid dynamics. Traditional ROMs often rely on linear assumptions that limit accuracy in complex flows. Here, we demonstrate how data-driven methods such as autoencoders, recurrent networks, and physics-informed learning can capture nonlinear dynamics more efficiently.

ğŸ“Œ Topics Covered:

Challenges of classical ROMs

How ML models capture spatiotemporal fluid behavior

Applications in flow control, turbulence and CFD acceleration

title: How big AI companies exploit data workers in Kenya | DW Documentary
description:
Behind today's AI revolution stands an invisible workforce: millions of data workers who painstakingly train artificial intelligence systems we all use. Many of them are based in the Global South, like Kenya. They are being exposed to traumatizing content and difficult work conditions, while earning a fraction of their counterparts in developed countries. But the tide is turning. These workers are breaking their silence, challenging the system, and demanding fair recognition in the world of AI.

In this video, Ameca, a humanoid with artificial intelligence, plays chess and... loses! Find out how AI reacts to an unexpected defeat and how it uses facial expressions and humor to create a lighthearted atmosphere. title: All Machine Learning Concepts Explained in 22 Minutes
description:

#########################################
I just started my own Patreon, in case you want to support!

#########################################

To get you out of your confusion with all the Machine Learning Vocabulary, here an overview of all basic terms you will encounter as you start your Journey in Machine Learning and Data Science.

title: Inside the Rise of AI-Driven Combat
description:
War will never be the same
Take the quiz to find your perfect trainer and get 14 days of free training here: https://go.trainwell.net/johnnyharris

AI is changing the way we fight wars. Not just in a hypothetical future, but right now. So letâ€™s take a look at what a battlefield looks like when one side is using AI and the other side isnâ€™t. 

Check out all my sources for this video here: https://docs.google.com/document/d/1owFj2cI6vtQMnAGmXjlC4jE6QXmcR4XZ3NmwfBd2i5M/edit?usp=sharing

If youâ€™re a student you can get access to The Economistâ€™s short form news app Espresso for free https://subscribenow.economist.com/student (not sponsored)

Special thanks to The Economist Team:
- Shashank Joshi, Defence Editor
- Liv Moloney, Head of Video
- Lee Mears, Art Director
- Anna Bucks, Executive Producer

Make sure to check out these articles from The Economist on AI Warfare:
- AI Will Transform the Character of Warfare: https://www.economist.com/leaders/2024/06/20/war-and-ai
- How AI is Changing Warfare: https://www.economist.com/briefing/2024/06/20/how-ai-is-changing-warfare


MORE CHANNELS:
Check out my new channel with Christophe Haubursin - Tunnel Vision  https://www.youtube.com/@christophe  
Check out my channel with Sam Ellis - Search Party  https://youtube.com/@SearchParty  

All the music for this video was created by our in-house composer Tom Fox and is available to license or just to listen to on our music channel Chromatic. Here's today's soundtrack: https://youtu.be/VfoYobvz6m8

Get access to behind-the-scenes vlogs, my scripts, and extended interviews over at https://www.patreon.com/johnnyharris

Do you have an insider tip or unique information on a story? Do you have a suggestion for a story you want us to cover? Submit to the Tip Line: https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSdpNs1ykIwd7KNkwntN897X_SX9hJ8WiTH_erlLU_bQp2GGLg/viewform?usp=sharing

AI Disclosure:  Occasionally, we use AI to create some of the imagery in our videos, which our (very talented) animators then spend weeks developing into what you see in the final video. When AI is used to generate any imagery that may appear onscreen, we'll add this to the video description. We're learning as we go about AI usage and transparency, and appreciate your thoughts.

About: 
Johnny Harris is an Emmy-winning independent journalist and contributor to the New York Times. Based in Washington, DC, Harris reports on interesting trends and stories domestically and around the globe, publishing to his audience of over 5 million on Youtube.  Harris produced and hosted the twice Emmy-nominated series Borders for Vox Media. His visual style blends motion graphics with cinematic videography to create content that explains complex issues in relatable ways.

title: Terence Tao: Hardest Problems in Mathematics, Physics & the Future of AI | Lex Fridman Podcast #472
description:
Terence Tao is widely considered to be one of the greatest mathematicians in history. He won the Fields Medal and the Breakthrough Prize in Mathematics, and has contributed to a wide range of fields from fluid dynamics with Navier-Stokes equations to mathematical physics & quantum mechanics, prime numbers & analytics number theory, harmonic analysis, compressed sensing, random matrix theory, combinatorics, and progress on many of the hardest problems in the history of mathematics.

title: La inteligencia artificial termina el vÃ­deo ğŸ˜±â€¼ï¸ | Iker Unzu
The AI Revolution Is Underhyped | Eric Schmidt | TED
description:
The arrival of non-human intelligence is a very big deal, says former Google CEO and chairman Eric Schmidt. In a wide-ranging interview with technologist Bilawal Sidhu, Schmidt makes the case that AI is wildly underhyped, as near-constant breakthroughs give rise to systems capable of doing even the most complex tasks on their own. He explores the staggering opportunities, sobering challenges and urgent risks of AI, showing why everyone will need to engage with this technology in order to remain relevant. (Recorded at TED2025 on April 11, 2025)

title: Get RICH with AI in Africa - Futurist Kwame
description:
Can technology truly transform Africa's future? Join us as Futurist Kwame, a visionary in tech and entrepreneurship, sheds light on the potential of technology to empower African youth. We explore the pressing need to move beyond traditional education, focusing on the critical skills required in today's competitive market, like VR marketing and the burgeoning cryptocurrency landscape. Through his extensive experience, Kwame offers a fresh perspective on overcoming skepticism around digital currencies and highlights opportunities for economic empowerment across the continent.

Are African societies ready to embrace a new way of thinking? Together, we challenge the cultural and religious barriers that often stifle innovation and self-sufficiency. We discuss how societal norms can hinder open-mindedness and adaptation, drawing a parallel with the evolving job market that prizes practical skills over mere credentials. By advocating for a kingdom-based mindset, we envision a future where communities thrive through empowerment and shared prosperity, underscoring the importance of personal responsibility and spiritual growth.

In a world driven by innovation, how do businesses stay ahead? Our conversation navigates the rapidly changing landscape of technology and business growth, with a spotlight on the transformative power of blockchain and digital transformation. From the potential of crypto wealth in Ghana to the essential role of R&D teams in enterprises, we offer insights on leveraging new technologies for competitive advantage. Listen as we weave personal stories of public speaking success and the pursuit of purpose, urging listeners to embrace change, find meaning through commitment, and recognize the limitless possibilities within Africa's vibrant landscape.

title: Will Your Job Still Exist in 2025? (New WEF Data Explained)
description:
Is your job about to radically change? The World Economic Forum just released their most comprehensive Future of Jobs Report ever, analyzing data from 1,000+ companies across 55 countries. And the findings are fascinating.

Rather than the usual "AI will take our jobs" narrative, we're seeing something much more interesting: the biggest transformation of work since the Industrial Revolution. By 2030, we'll see 170 million new jobs created and 92 million jobs transformed. But here's the twist - it's not just about job loss or creation. It's about evolution.

In this deep-dive video, we break down exactly how this transformation is happening and what it means for your career. Using exclusive data and real-world examples, we'll explore how jobs are changing across every industry and what skills you'll need to stay ahead.

ğŸ” In this video, you'll discover:
âœ“ Why 59% of workers will need completely new skills by 2030
âœ“ The surprising truth about AI creating more jobs than it eliminates
âœ“ Which industries are growing fastest (and which are declining)
âœ“ The 5 most valuable skills employers will want in 2025
âœ“ How jobs you think are "safe" might transform completely
âœ“ Real examples of how humans and AI will work together
âœ“ Practical steps to prepare for the changing job market

description:
Descubriendo la Inteligencia Artificial Generativa: MÃ¡s AllÃ¡ de los Deepfakes
La Inteligencia Artificial (IA) ha alcanzado niveles impresionantes en los Ãºltimos aÃ±os, y una de las Ã¡reas mÃ¡s fascinantes es la IA generativa. Seguramente has escuchado hablar de ChatGPT, Midjourney, prompts y deepfakes, pero Â¿realmente sabes quÃ© implica la IA generativa?

Â¿QuÃ© es la IA generativa?
La IA generativa es un campo que se centra en la creaciÃ³n de contenido nuevo por parte de algoritmos de inteligencia artificial. Esto puede incluir la generaciÃ³n de textos, imÃ¡genes, videos, mÃºsica e incluso voces. Para lograr esto, se utiliza lo que se conoce como "prompt", una descripciÃ³n de lo que se desea crear que se introduce en una interfaz de chat. A partir de esta descripciÃ³n, las herramientas de IA generativa proporcionan respuestas, resumen informaciÃ³n y generan ideas diversas de manera rÃ¡pida y eficiente.

El proceso creativo detrÃ¡s de la IA generativa
La base de este proceso creativo radica en la ingente cantidad de datos a los que accede el sistema de IA para identificar patrones y similitudes. Es impresionante cÃ³mo la IA puede producir contenido completamente nuevo que a menudo resulta difÃ­cil de distinguir de lo creado por seres humanos. Desde breves relatos hasta composiciones musicales, las posibilidades son infinitas.

Los peligros del mal uso de la IA generativa
Sin embargo, como sucede con cualquier avance tecnolÃ³gico, la IA generativa tambiÃ©n puede ser objeto de mal uso. Los "deepfakes" son un ejemplo preocupante de cÃ³mo la IA se puede utilizar para producir imÃ¡genes o videos que parecen reales. AdemÃ¡s, los textos generados por IA pueden ser difÃ­ciles de distinguir como creados por una mÃ¡quina. Es crucial estar conscientes de este fenÃ³meno, conocido como "alucinaciÃ³n", donde la IA puede proporcionar respuestas que suenan correctas pero que en realidad son incorrectas.

Utilizando la IA generativa de manera responsable
Para aprovechar al mÃ¡ximo la IA generativa, es fundamental aprender a guiar las herramientas con prompts significativos y utilizarlas de manera reflexiva. Si bien la IA puede servir como un valioso compaÃ±ero en la escritura o el aprendizaje, es esencial que los humanos sean responsables de verificar la veracidad de los hechos. La IA puede encargarse de tareas complejas, pero la responsabilidad Ãºltima recae en nosotros.

ConclusiÃ³n
En resumen, la IA generativa es una herramienta poderosa que tiene el potencial de transformar numerosos aspectos de nuestra vida. Desde la creaciÃ³n de contenido hasta la detecciÃ³n de fraudes, sus aplicaciones son infinitas. Sin embargo, debemos recordar que con este gran poder tambiÃ©n viene una gran responsabilidad. Es fundamental utilizar la IA generativa de manera Ã©tica y responsable, asegurÃ¡ndonos de que siempre se utilice para el bien comÃºn.

title: "I'm sorry, I don't have a plane to give you," South African president tells Trump
description: South African President Cyril Ramaphosa met with U.S. President Donald Trump at the White House on Wednesday. During the meeting, Ramaphosa joked and told Trump: "I'm sorry I don't have a plane to give you." Trump responded, "I wish you did. I would take it. If your country offered the United States Air Force a plane, I would take it."

title: Machine Learning Explained! Types of Machine Learning? #machinelearning #ai
What AI Can Replace: The Future of Jobs and Automation
description:
As we delve into the realm of cutting-edge technology, it's essential to explore the future of jobs and automation. The rapid advancement of artificial intelligence has sparked concerns about the potential replacement of human labor. From robotics to machine learning, AI is revolutionizing industries and transforming the workforce. But what does this mean for the economy and the future of work? In this video, we'll examine the impact of automation on various sectors, including entertainment, research, and business. We'll also discuss the role of innovators like Elon Musk and companies like Boston Dynamics in shaping the AI revolution. Join us as we uncover the insights and knowledge necessary to navigate the changing landscape of work and prepare for the future skills required to thrive in an era of smart technology. The question is, what AI can replace, and how will it affect the future of jobs and the economy?

AI is changing the world, but is it coming for your job? From robots in factories to self-checkouts in stores, automation is replacing human workers faster than ever. But what jobs are at risk, and which ones are still safe?  

Chapters:  
00:00:00 - Introduction: AI's Impact on Jobs and the Economy  
00:00:40 - Jobs Already Replaced by AI  
00:01:20 - Industries That Are Rapidly Changing  
00:02:00 - What AI Can't Replace (Yet)  
00:02:40 - The Future: How to Adapt to an AI-Driven World  

AI has already taken over roles in manufacturing, customer service, and transportation. Self-checkout machines are replacing cashiers, chatbots are handling customer service, and self-driving cars are being tested for deliveries. Even creative fields aren't safe, with AI generating art, music, and writing.  

But AI has its limits. It struggles with complex human interactions, emotional intelligence, and unpredictable situations. Jobs like therapists, emergency responders, and teachers still require human adaptability and intuition that machines can't replicate-at least not yet.  

As AI evolves, industries will continue to shift. Instead of fearing job loss, experts suggest focusing on **learning new skills, adapting to AI-driven tools, and working alongside automation**. The future workforce won't just be human or machine-it'll be a mix of both.  

So, what do you think? Should we embrace AI in the workplace, or are we heading toward an automation crisis? Let us know in the comments! Don't forget to like, subscribe, and hit the notification bell for more insights into the future of technology.

Obs: No Linux existe um passo extra. ApÃ³s baixar o Docker Desktop, vocÃª precisarÃ¡ abrir um terminal (CMD) e executar o comando:

2ï¸âƒ£ Baixe o arquivo docker-compose.yml do Github:

Nos seus downloads, crie uma nova pasta com nome "N8N WAHA Local" ou parecido, e coloque o arquivo docker-compose.yml dentro dela.

4ï¸âƒ£ Conectar seu Whatsapp no WAHA:

ApÃ³s baixar tudo, abra o aplicativo Docker Desktop e vocÃª verÃ¡ uma nova stack de containers com os aplicativos N8N e WAHA, e os bancos de dados Redis e Postgres. Para acessÃ¡-los basta clicar na porta do container atravÃ©s da tabela de exibiÃ§Ã£o (formato xxxx:xxxx).

5ï¸âƒ£ Configurar o N8N:

ApÃ³s entrar no WAHA com seu Whatsapp, volte ao aplicativo do Docker Desktop e acesse o N8N, clicando na porta 5678:5678 e faÃ§a as configuraÃ§Ãµes da sua conta.

ApÃ³s criar a conta, informe um e-mail para receber uma chave de ativaÃ§Ã£o gratuita do N8N. Isso irÃ¡ te ajudar liberando algumas funÃ§Ãµes extras.

ApÃ³s ativar o N8N, vÃ¡ para o painel "Community Nodes" (do lado esquerdo da tela, ainda em settings), clique em "Install a community node" e digite:

6ï¸âƒ£ Montar o Workflow:

Teste e depois adicione um novo node, dessa vez um "Switch" em frente ao SET. Neste switch apenas faÃ§a a comparaÃ§Ã£o, se o "event" for igual a "message" e siga o fluxo normal.

Adicione o node do AI Agent e faÃ§a as configuraÃ§Ãµes de prompt, system prompt, chat model e memory.

A configuraÃ§Ã£o do node do Redis Chat Memory Ã© a seguinte:

Depois adicione um Node do WAHA para visualizar a mensagem, passando as configuraÃ§Ãµes de SessÃ£o, Chat ID e Payload ID.

E por fim, adicione um Node do WAHA para responder a mensagem, passando as configuraÃ§Ãµes de SessÃ£o, Chat ID e TEXT, onde TEXT Ã© o Output gerado pelo node do Agente de IA.

title: The Future of AI: Will It Save Humanity or Replace Us? | Animated Tech Story
description:
What happens when machines outthink their makers?
In this gripping anime-style video, explore the rise of artificial intelligenceâ€”from helpful robots to deepfakes, job automation, and the moral dilemmas we now face. Featuring global trends and warnings from leaders like Elon Musk, this short film blends powerful visuals with critical insight into the future of humanity and technology.

From Silicon Valley to Tokyo, AI is reshaping everything: healthcare, finance, jobs, and even creativity. Is this the dawn of progressâ€”or a digital turning point? Perfect for American viewers and global tech enthusiasts alike.

title: Fort Madison, Iowa, USA | - Virtual Railfan
description:
Static Cam (Members Only):     https://youtube.com/live/P1ajNE3v9BE
PTZ Cam (Chat):                          https://youtube.com/live/L6eG4ahJc_Q
Bridge Cam PTZ (members):    https://www.youtube.com/live/_0JYnfB6SWw
Bridge Static Cam :                     https://www.youtube.com/live/DuXSP6y9W7U

Actual start date: June 26, 2020

You are watching a live stream of Fort Madison, Iowa, USA, for people who enjoy watching trains. You are welcome to join our family friendly chat. Please check out the rules below. 

Special thanks to the Kingsley Inn for sponsoring and hosting the camera! They love the train buffs who stay with them on their railfanning trips, and it shows in their hospitality! Find out more about the beautiful Kingsley Inn: https://www.kingsley-inn.com or visit them on Facebook for frequent updates:  https://www.facebook.com/thekingsleyinniowa

Burlington Northern Santa Fe Railway Signal Rules  link
https://bit.ly/3l7idtS

Duplication or distribution of our videos is STRICTLY prohibited without permission. Official policy here: https://virtualrailfan.com/recording

CHAT RULES:
â€¢ Be polite and respectful 
â€¢ Please use English, we need a single language to be able to understand each other. If youâ€™re not fluent, use a translator such as Google Translate: https://translate.google.com 
â€¢ Donâ€™t post in ALL CAPS or use excessive emojis, letters or characters. 
â€¢ Donâ€™t discuss politics, religion, race, sex, violence, disturbing details about train or vehicle accidents, or anything like that. We try to be mindful of any children who may be watching. 
â€¢ Don't use the terms "foamer" or "foaming" in your comments or your username. Many railfans find them derogatory and offensive. 
â€¢ The conversation here is trains, and please remember that it needs to come first. 
â€¢ Please keep conversations of personal issues (medical, domestic, legal, etc.) out of the chat; take it to messaging or email. Remember, you are sharing information with hundreds of people, not just those directly involved in the chat.
â€¢ Donâ€™t ask to become a moderator. Itâ€™s earned. If weâ€™re interested in your assistance, we will contact you. 
â€¢ Please donâ€™t use our chats to seek attention, stand on your soapbox, or criticize other peopleâ€™s presences or contributions
â€¢ Please do not demand movements of the camera.  The moderators will pan the 360 cameras at their discretion and according to the guidelines they have been given. It's ok to alert the cam op to upcoming trains. 
â€¢ Just be nice, itâ€™s amazing what happens when weâ€™re all nice to each other. 

THINGS THAT WILL GET YOU BANNED: 
â€¢ Inappropriate usernames or avatar
â€¢ Profanity
â€¢ Coming into chat for the sole purpose of asking for subscriptions (subs) or to blatantly promote your channel
â€¢ Being intentionally disruptive, creating arguments or any other jerk-like behavior 
â€¢ Not following the moderatorsâ€™ instructions 
â€¢ Blocking a moderator (including Nightbot)

ABOUT THIS FEED:
There are 3 tracks visible here.  The 2 farthest from the camera are the BNSF Chillicothe Subdivision which is part of the BNSF Southern Transcon.  The BNSF Fort Madison Yard is about 1.5 miles to the West. The BNSF Marceline Subdivision begins there and continues West to Kansas City. UP also has trackage rights here. The Amtrak Southwest Chief passes twice daily, once in each direction. The Fort Madison Toll Bridge to the east of camera is a swinging truss bridge over the Mississippi River that connects Fort Madison, Iowa, and Niota, Illinois. Rail traffic occupies the lower deck of the bridge, while two lanes of road traffic occupy the upper deck.  FRA documents an average of 65 trains per day. The track closest to the camera is the BNSF Hannibal Sub, commonly known as the K-Line.  It runs between Burlington IA and St. Louis, MO.

Informational Map of the Marceline Sub: http://www.curtlundgren.com/la_plata.jpg (Courtesy of Curt Lundgren, thanks Curt!)

Fort Madison area railroad radio feed:     https://www.broadcastify.com/webPlayer/40143==

Train log:  https://bit.ly/4mdS78G
Virtual Railfan and our mods are not affiliated with train logs, they are maintained by volunteers. Please reach out to them outside of our chats for more detailed information or to discuss the mechanics of logging. Thanks to everyone who contributes faithfully to it!

Whenâ€™s the next train? Yeah, we get this a lot. You can figure out the next Amtrak passenger train with this handy link:  http://bit.ly/31bn58V

ABOUT VIRTUAL RAILFAN: 
For everything Virtual Railfan follow this link:
https://linktr.ee/virtualrailfan

Full VRF Cam List:   http://bit.ly/3FROxxw

Comments?  Send them to community@virtualrailfan.com

About AWGP :-

Shantikunj Ashram, located in the tranquil city of Haridwar, India, serves as the spiritual headquarters of the All World Gayatri Pariwar (AWGP), a global movement founded by the visionary Pandit Shriram Sharma Acharya in 1971. The ashram stands as a beacon of spiritual awakening, moral rejuvenation, and social transformation, rooted in the philosophy of the Gayatri Mantra and the principles of scientific spirituality.

Under the guidance of Pandit Shriram Sharma Acharya, Shantikunj has become a center for personal transformation, where individuals are encouraged to harmonize their inner and outer worlds. His teachings emphasize spiritual empowerment through meditation, moral development through virtuous living, and social responsibility through service and environmental sustainability. His efforts have inspired millions worldwide to embrace a life of purpose, righteousness, and community service.

After Pandit Shriram Sharma Acharya's mahaprayan, his legacy was carried forward by Shraddhya Dr. Pranav Pandya and Shraddhya Shail Jiji. As the current heads of the All World Gayatri Pariwar (AWGP), Shraddhya Dr. Pranav Pandya and Shraddhya Shail Jiji have expanded Shantikunj's global outreach, promoting the values of compassion, peace, and universal harmony. They continue to guide the organizationâ€™s work in social welfare, educational initiatives, and environmental conservation, all grounded in the timeless wisdom of the Vedas and the Gayatri Mantra.

Dr. Chinmay Pandya, serving as the youth representative of AWGP, Dr. Pranav Pandya to engage the younger generation in the mission of Shantikunj. His focus is on fostering a sense of community, purpose, and spiritual connection among youth, ensuring the continuity of the ashram's transformative message for future generations.

Together, the leaders of Shantikunj Ashram continue to inspire a global movement aimed at creating a world based on spiritual, ethical, and social values. Through their leadership, Shantikunj remains a sanctuary for those seeking inner peace, personal growth, and a deeper understanding of their role in the world.

A robotic boy, the first programmed to love, David (Haley Joel Osment) is adopted as a test case by a Cybertronics employee (Sam Robards) and his wife (Frances O'Connor). title: The Future of AI Technology: Predictions and Potential Impacts (3 Minutes)
description:
In this thought-provoking video, we explore "The Future of AI Technology: Predictions and Potential Impacts." Artificial Intelligence is rapidly evolving, and its influence on various sectors is becoming increasingly significant. In this video, we will discuss key predictions for the future of AI technology, including its potential impact on jobs, healthcare, education, and more. You'll learn about the innovations that are set to change our lives and address common misconceptions surrounding AI. Whether you're a tech enthusiast, a professional in the field, or simply curious about the future, this video will provide you with essential insights into the transformative power of AI technology. Join us as we delve into the exciting possibilities that lie ahead!

In a quiet home, an orange anthropomorphic cat, his blue feline wife, and their little blue kitten slept peacefully. Suddenly, the baby vomited in his sleep, and the father's hand landed in the mess. With nowhere to go, the mother cat desperately found a job as a waitress at a restaurant. But fate struck againâ€”she slipped on a wet floor while serving, ruining the food and getting fired on the spot. Heartbroken and in tears, she wandered the streets with her baby until she knocked on the door of a luxurious home, hoping to find work as a maid. Moved by her dedication and struggle, he soon began helping her moreâ€”giving her money and even enrolling her son in school. But just when life seemed to get better, her abusive husband reappeared, stole all the money, and left her crying once again. Seeing her pain, the white cat comforted her and continued to support her. When the violent husband returned once more demanding money, the white cat stood up to him and called the police. The authorities arrested the abusive cat, finally freeing the mother from fear. In time, love blossomed between the white and blue cats. They got married and built a new, peaceful life togetherâ€”raising her baby in a home filled with kindness, safety, and love.

title: Current Realities and Future Prospects of AI
description:
Ready to unravel the mysteries of AI? Listen in as we explores the fascinating world of artificial intelligence. This episode delves into the impact of AI on real estate, from predictive analytics to the future of property management and will help you discover the implications for jobs, positive transformations in real estate investing, and the challenges we face at the intersection of AI, automation, and "if then" bots.

AI in Real Estate: Learn about AI's impact on real estate, covering predictive analytics and the future of property management.

title: Theyâ€™ve arrivedâ€”jobs, cities, and lives are shifting fast.
description:
In the world of cutting-edge technology and innovation, the question on everyone's mind is: Will Robots Replace Humans Or Become Our Helpers? Join us as we delve into the latest advancements in AI, robotics, and automation, featuring breakthroughs from pioneers like Tesla, Boston Dynamics, and OpenAI. From humanoid robots like Atlas and Unitree to the futuristic Tesla Optimus, we'll explore the potential of artificial intelligence to revolutionize industries and transform our daily lives. With insights from experts in the field, we'll examine the possibilities and challenges of AI integration, and what it means for the future of work and humanity. Get ready for a fascinating journey into the world of AI news, tech breakthroughs, and the future of technology.

The world of robotics is evolving faster than ever, with artificial intelligence and automation shaping the future of industries, jobs, and even daily life. Are we approaching an era where machines replace human workers entirely, or will technology and humans coexist in new ways?  

Chapters:  
00:00:00 - Introduction: The Rise of Advanced Robotics  
00:00:40 - Robotics in 2025: What's Changing?  
00:01:20 - The Impact of Automation on Jobs  
00:02:00 - Benefits and Risks of an AI-Driven World  
00:02:30 - Can Humans and Machines Coexist?  

From robotic surgeons to self-driving cars, AI-powered machines are already transforming industries. Factories rely on robotic arms, AI chatbots replace customer service agents, and self-learning algorithms optimize logistics, finance, and even creative work. But with automation replacing human labor at an accelerating pace, what does this mean for the future of employment?  

Some experts believe automation will create new jobs, shifting workers into more creative and specialized roles. Others worry that AI and robotics will eliminate millions of jobs, leading to economic and social upheaval. Will humans adapt, or will robots surpass us in ways we never expected?  

Beyond work, advanced robotics could reshape how we live. Humanoid robots are being designed for caregiving, customer service, and even companionship. Smart homes and AI assistants continue to evolve, making life easier but also raising concerns about privacy and dependency on technology.  

While AI and automation offer incredible benefits-like precision in medical procedures, efficiency in industries, and enhanced safety-there are also risks. Ethical dilemmas, security concerns, and the loss of human control over AI-driven systems remain hot topics. Could we reach a point where machines surpass human intelligence and make decisions on their own?  

So, will advanced robotics replace us, or will they simply change how we live and work? The answer may depend on how we integrate and regulate these technologies. The future of AI and robotics is unfolding now-are we ready for what comes next?  

What's your take? Are robots a threat, an opportunity, or something in between? Let us know in the comments! Don't forget to like, subscribe, and hit the notification bell for more deep dives into the future of technology.  

Comment, Subscribe and Like! ğŸ‘
Don't forget to watch our other videos! ğŸ“º
Let us know in the comments what topics interest you! ğŸ“

AGI Explained: Is True Human-Level AI Closer Than You Think?
description:
Could a machine someday think, reason, and plan like a human? Not just respond to commands...but act, adapt, and set its own goals? Thatâ€™s the dreamâ€”and fearâ€”of AGI.

In this video, we dive deep into one of the biggest questions in tech and humanity: What is AGI, and how close are we to building it?

Unlike todayâ€™s narrow AIâ€”like ChatGPT or Alexaâ€”Artificial General Intelligence would be capable of learning any task a human can, transferring knowledge between domains, improving itself over time, and making decisions with minimal human input. It wouldnâ€™t just complete tasksâ€”it would understand context, anticipate needs, and operate across multiple modalities: vision, language, robotics, and beyond.

ğŸ¯ What youâ€™ll learn in this video:

The difference between narrow AI and AGI (and why it matters)
How systems like DeepMindâ€™s Gato, Anthropicâ€™s Claude, and OpenAIâ€™s GPT-4 are pushing us closer
The rise of agentic AIâ€”tools like Auto-GPT and Devin that act autonomously
Why tasks like memory, embodiment, and alignment are still unsolved
Real-world examples, timelines from researchers, and what AGI could mean for you

We also explore the risks and opportunities that AGI presents:
How it could revolutionize work, education, medicine, and creativity
How it might widen inequality or escape our control if built irresponsibly
And the urgent need for alignment, governance, and safety protocols

Whether you're a developer, researcher, policymaker, or just AI-curious, this is the full picture: technical breakthroughs, big open questions, and why AGI could be the most transformative (and controversial) invention of our lifetime.

Wie gut ist Europa auf einen mÃ¶glichen Krieg mit Russland vorbereitet? Drohnen, autonome Waffen und KÃ¼nstliche Intelligenz kÃ¶nnten das Schlachtfeld der Zukunft revolutionieren. Wird neue Technik den entscheidenden Unterschied im Kampf um die Vorherrschaft machen? 

Das Schlachtfeld der Zukunft wird vom Computer aus gesteuert. Lassen sich so Kriege gewinnen? Worauf kommt es wirklich an?

In den ersten Monaten des Ukrainekrieges wurden Tausende russische Panzer von modernen westlichen Panzerabwehrwaffen abgeschossen. Die russischen Panzer scheinen technisch Ã¼berholt. Doch neue russische Modelle sind bereits in der Produktion. Darauf muss der Westen reagieren â€“ mit neuen Panzern, mit noch besserem Schutz vor Lenkwaffen. Doch bis sie entwickelt und gebaut sind, kann es noch Jahre dauern.

Die Bundeswehr bereitet sich intensiv auf mÃ¶gliche Konflikte vor. Deutsche Soldaten Ã¼ben am Polarkreis in Norwegen. In Litauen wird erstmals eine Garnison einer deutschen Brigade aufgebaut. Etwa 5.000 deutsche Soldaten sollen dort stationiert werden. 

â€Wenn wir sehen, dass wir laut unserer Analysten fÃ¼nf bis acht Jahre Zeit haben, bis die russischen StreitkrÃ¤fte sich so rekonstituiert haben, dass ein Angriff gegen das NATO-Territorium mÃ¶glich wÃ¤re, (â€¦) dann mÃ¼ssen wir in fÃ¼nf Jahren fertig sein. Das ist 2029â€œ, sagt Generalinspekteur Carsten Breuer, der oberste Soldat der Bundeswehr.

title: Die simple Aufgabe, an der jede KI scheitert
description:
ğŸ§  Entdecke modernbrain: âš¡â¯â¯ https://modernbrain.de â®â®âš¡
(Anzeige) 

â–ºAlle Videos: http://bit.ly/1fa7Tw3

KÃ¼nstliche Intelligenzen entwickeln sich in atemberaubendem Tempo und Ã¼bertreffen den Menschen lÃ¤ngst in vielen Bereichen. KI-Assistenten wie ChatGPT, Google Gemini oder xAI Grok sind bereits alltÃ¤glich geworden. KI-Agenten und Humanoide Roboter werden durch AI-Technologien immer alltagstauglicher. Als entscheidender Durchbruch gelten dabei die sogenannten â€Advanced Reasoningâ€œ-Modelle. Fragen wir die KI etwas, durchlÃ¤uft sie zunÃ¤chst einen inneren Denkprozess, in dem sie Ã¼berlegt und reflektiert, bis sie entscheidet eine Antwort geben zu kÃ¶nnen. Sowohl die Entwicklung der KIs als auch die Erforschung der neuronalen Netze in unseren Gehirnen legen nahe, dass Computer ab einer hinreichenden KomplexitÃ¤t ein Bewusstsein entwickeln kÃ¶nnten. Gleichzeitig deuten die Erkenntnisse darauf hin, dass auch unser menschliches Bewusstsein nichts weiter als ein Produkt komplexer Berechnungen und Algorithmen sein kÃ¶nnte. Doch gerade in den tiefsten Grundstrukturen der Mathematik finden wir einen starken Hinweis darauf, dass menschliches Bewusstsein mehr ist als ein Algorithmus. Denn selbst die besten kÃ¼nstliche Intelligenzen versagen an verblÃ¼ffend einfachen Dingen: sogenannten GÃ¶delsÃ¤tzen. Das sind simple Aussagen, die Menschen verstehen kÃ¶nnen, aber an denen selbst die fortschrittlichsten KIs der Zukunft immer scheitern werden. Dies zeigt, dass das menschliche Verstehen und somit das Bewusstsein, mehr ist als ein Algorithmus jemals leisten kann. Wie kann das sein? Und was sind diese GÃ¶delsÃ¤tze?


Noch ein Hinweis zum Inhalt des Videos: Genau genommen gibt es auch sehr einfache Systeme von Axiomen in denen jeder wahre Satz beweisbar ist. Damit GÃ¶dels Theorie gilt, mÃ¼ssen die Axiome komplex genug sein, damit sich darin die natÃ¼rlichen Zahlen wie 1,2,3,4... konstruieren lassen.


Quellen und mehr zum Thema:

- The Emperorâ€™s New Mind â€“ Roger Penrose
- Xu, Frank F., et al. "Theagentcompany: benchmarking llm agents on consequential real world tasks." arXiv preprint arXiv:2412.14161 (2024).

What is Prompt Engineering?

Prompt engineering involves optimizing artificial intelligence engineering for multiple purposes. It includes refining large language models (LLMs) using specific prompts and recommended outputs. Additionally, it focuses on enhancing input to different generative AI services to make text or images. With advancements in generative AI tools, prompt engineering becomes crucial for generating diverse content, such as robotic process automation bots, 3D assets, scripts, robot instructions, and various digital artifacts.
- - - - - - - - - - - - - - 

What kinds of jobs can you get with Prompt Engineering skills?â€

Here are some potential job roles:

Machine Learning Engineer
Data Scientist
Natural Language Processing (NLP) Engineer
AI Research Scientist
Software Engineer (AI/ML)
Data Engineer
Content Generation Specialist
Conversational AI Developer
AI Product Manager
AI Ethicist

Remember that the job market and the demand for specific skills can change over time, so staying updated on industry trends and job postings is essential. 

- - - - - - - - - - - - - - 

Who are the instructors for Prompt Engineering Course?

All the instructors at edureka are practitioners from the Industry with minimum 10-12 yrs of relevant IT experience. They are subject matter experts and are trained by edureka for providing an awesome learning experience to the participants.

title: AI and Jobs Debate is Spiraling: Here are 5+ Skills that Pay
description:
My site: https://natebjones.com/
My links: https://linktr.ee/natebjones
My substack: https://natesnewsletter.substack.com/

Takeaways
 1. Pascalâ€™s Career Wager: Treat the AI-and-jobs debate like Pascalâ€™s wagerâ€”prepare for any outcome by investing in skills that pay off whether automation explodes or stalls.
 2. Solve High-Quality Problems: The safest hedge is becoming excellent at spotting and solving complex, high-value problems; that value endures in both optimistic and pessimistic futures.
 3. Agency Over Fear: High-agency professionals who act, learn, and adapt will outperform those who doom-scroll and wait for clarity. Action is the low-risk option.
 4. Human Skills Resurge: Emotional clarity, discernment, and genuine connection are rising in importance as interviews and work shift back in person to verify â€œyouâ€™re not an LLM.â€
 5. Signal Beyond Perfect Resumes: AI has commoditized flawless rÃ©sumÃ©s; differentiated proof now comes from shipping real projects and demonstrating end-to-end problem ownership.
 6. Low-Regret Skill Investment: Strengthening meta-skillsâ€”problem recognition, solution design, resource marshalling, execution, integrationâ€”never hurts and often future-proofs a career.

Quotes
â€œWe should treat AI careers like Pascalâ€™s wager: act as if agency always matters, because it does.â€
â€œHigh-agency people donâ€™t work harderâ€”they run around obstacles the rest of us stare at.â€
â€œIn a world of perfect rÃ©sumÃ©s, real signal is shipping something that actually works.â€

Summary
I argue that the AI-jobs debate is a distraction; like Pascalâ€™s wager, the rational move is to build skills that win either way. Whether Dario Amodeiâ€™s forecast of vanishing entry-level jobs proves right or Gergely Oroszâ€™s optimism prevails, careers hinge on high agency and the ability to solve complex problems. That means sharpening meta-skills, shipping tangible projects, and cultivating human strengthsâ€”emotional clarity, discernment, authentic connectionâ€”as interviews return in person. Perfect rÃ©sumÃ©s are now meaningless; demonstrable impact and adaptable wisdom carry real signal. Prepare, act, and you de-risk your future instead of betting on headlines. (100 words)

Keywords
AI jobs, Pascalâ€™s wager, high agency, problem solving, meta-skills, human skills, emotional clarity, in-person interviews, rÃ©sumÃ© signal, Dario Amodei, Gergely Orosz, entry-level automation, career strategy, GitHub projects, fear vs action
